\vec{r}
\frac12 \frac{d}{dt}|\vec{r}|^2 = \vec{r} \cdot \vec{r}' = \vec{r} \cdot ( \vec{C} \times \vec{r} ) = 0 \quad\implies\quad |\vec{r}| = \text{ constant. }
